Description: 3M Company is a diversified technology company with a global presence. It manufactures and markets a wide range of products and services in various sectors, including industrial, healthcare, consumer goods, and safety.
A. O. Smith Corporation manufactures and markets water heaters and boilers. It also produces water treatment products for residential and commercial applications. The company operates globally.

Abbott Laboratories discovers, develops, manufactures, and sells a broad line of health care products. It operates in four segments: Established Pharmaceutical Products, Medical Devices, Diagnostics, and Nutritionals. The company's products range from diagnostics and medical devices to nutritional products and branded generic pharmaceuticals.

AbbVie Inc. is a research-based biopharmaceutical company. It discovers, develops, manufactures, and sells pharmaceuticals worldwide. The company focuses on treating conditions such as chronic autoimmune diseases, oncology, and neurological disorders.

Accenture plc is a global professional services company, providing a broad range of services and solutions in strategy, consulting, digital, technology and operations. It partners with clients to become high-performance businesses and governments.

Adobe Inc. is a multinational computer software company. It is known for its software products for creating and publishing a wide range of content, including graphics, photography, illustration, animation, multimedia/video, motion pictures, and print.

Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) is a global semiconductor company that designs and manufactures computer processors and related technologies. Its products include central processing units (CPUs), graphics processing units (GPUs), and field-programmable gate arrays (FPGAs), serving markets such as gaming, data centers, and personal computers.

The AES Corporation is a global power generation and utility company. It generates and distributes electrical power, using a diverse range of fuels and technologies, including renewable sources like solar, wind, and energy storage.

Aflac Incorporated is an insurance company providing supplemental health and life insurance. The company operates through Aflac Japan and Aflac U.S., offering various insurance products to protect individuals and families from financial hardship.

Agilent Technologies Inc. is a life sciences and diagnostics company. It provides application focused solutions that include instruments, software, services, and consumables for the entire laboratory workflow. Its solutions serve markets including life sciences, diagnostics, and applied chemical.

Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. provides industrial gases and related equipment and applications worldwide. It serves customers in various industries, including refining, chemical, metals, electronics, manufacturing, and food and beverage.

Airbnb, Inc. operates an online marketplace for lodging, primarily facilitating short-term homestays and experiences. It connects hosts with guests seeking accommodations and activities worldwide. The company earns revenue through service fees charged to both hosts and guests.

Akamai Technologies, Inc. is a global content delivery network (CDN), cybersecurity, and cloud service company. It provides a platform for delivering web content and applications over the Internet, enhancing website performance and security.

Albemarle Corporation develops, manufactures, and markets engineered specialty chemicals worldwide. It operates through three segments: Lithium, Bromine Specialties, and Catalysts. The company's products are used in lithium batteries, flame retardants, and catalysts.

Alexandria Real Estate Equities, Inc. is a real estate investment trust (REIT) focused on collaborative life science, agtech, and technology campuses in innovation cluster locations. The company provides space and capital to accelerate the growth of companies engaged in advancing human health and improving nutrition.

Align Technology designs, manufactures, and markets Invisalign clear aligners and iTero intraoral scanners and services. Invisalign clear aligners are used by orthodontists and general practitioner dentists to straighten teeth without metal braces. iTero scanners are used to create digital impressions for restorative dentistry and orthodontics.

Allegion PLC is a global provider of security products and solutions. The company manufactures and sells mechanical and electronic security products, including locks, exit devices, door closers, and access control systems. Allegion serves a variety of end markets, including commercial, residential, and institutional.

Alliant Energy Corporation is a public utility holding company. It provides regulated electricity and natural gas service to customers in the Midwest. The company also invests in renewable energy projects.

The Allstate Corporation is a major U.S. insurer. It provides a broad array of property and casualty insurance, life insurance, and retirement and investment products. Allstate sells insurance under the Allstate, Esurance, and Encompass brands.

Alphabet Inc. is a holding company. Google LLC is Alphabet's largest subsidiary. Google is a global technology company focused on search, advertising, operating systems and platforms, enterprise and hardware products.

Google (GOOG) is a multinational technology company focusing on search engine technology, online advertising, cloud computing, software, and hardware. It is considered one of the Big Five companies in the American information technology industry.

Altria Group, Inc. engages in the manufacture and sale of cigarettes, smokeless products, and wine in the United States. Its portfolio includes Marlboro cigarettes, Black & Mild cigars, Copenhagen and Skoal smokeless tobacco, and various wine brands.

Amazon.com, Inc. is an American multinational technology company focusing on e-commerce, cloud computing, online advertising, digital streaming, and artificial intelligence. It is one of the Big Five American information technology companies.

Amcor plc develops, manufactures, and sells various packaging products in Europe, North America, Latin America, Asia Pacific, and internationally. It offers rigid packaging, flexible packaging, specialty cartons, closures, and services for food, beverage, pharmaceutical, medical, home and personal care, and other consumer products.

Ameren Corporation is a public utility holding company. It provides energy services to 2.4 million electric and 900,000 natural gas customers in Illinois and Missouri. The company operates through regulated and non-regulated segments.

American Electric Power (AEP) is a major investor-owned electric public utility holding company. It engages in the generation, transmission, and distribution of electricity to customers in multiple states. AEP also focuses on renewable energy and energy efficiency initiatives.
American Express Company is a global financial services company. It provides charge and credit payment card products, and travel-related services to consumers and businesses worldwide.

American International Group, Inc. (AIG) is a leading global insurance organization. It provides a wide range of property casualty insurance, life insurance, retirement solutions, and other financial services to customers in more than 80 countries and jurisdictions.

American Tower Corporation is a real estate investment trust (REIT) and a leading independent owner, operator and developer of multitenant communications real estate. It owns, operates, and develops wireless and broadcast communications infrastructure in several countries worldwide. The company's primary business is leasing antenna space on its towers to wireless service providers, government entities, and broadcasters.

American Water Works Company, Inc., through its subsidiaries, provides water and wastewater services. It supplies clean, safe, and reliable water and wastewater services to approximately 14 million people in 24 states.

Ameriprise Financial, Inc. provides a range of financial products and services to individual and institutional clients in the United States and internationally. It operates through Advice & Wealth Management, Asset Management, Retirement & Protection Solutions, and Corporate & Other segments.
AMETEK, Inc. is a global manufacturer of electronic instruments and electromechanical devices. The company sells its products to the process, aerospace, power, and industrial markets.

Amgen Inc. is a biotechnology company that discovers, develops, manufactures, and delivers human therapeutics. It focuses on areas such as oncology, cardiovascular disease, inflammation, bone health, and nephrology.

Amphenol Corporation is a leading global provider of interconnect, antenna, and sensor solutions. The company designs, manufactures, and markets a broad range of products for various industries, including communications, aerospace, industrial, and automotive.

Analog Devices, Inc. designs, manufactures, tests, and markets a broad portfolio of high-performance analog, mixed-signal, and digital signal processing integrated circuits used in virtually all types of electronic equipment. The company focuses on key strategic markets including industrial, automotive, communications, and consumer.

ANSYS, Inc. develops and markets engineering simulation software and services used by engineers, designers, researchers, and students across various industries. Their solutions enable users to predict how product designs will behave in real-world environments.

Aon plc is a global professional services firm providing a broad range of risk, retirement and health solutions. The company empowers clients to reduce volatility and improve performance via data-driven insights.
APA Corporation is an independent energy company that explores for, develops, and produces crude oil and natural gas. The company has operations in the United States, Egypt, and the United Kingdom.
Apollo Global Management, Inc. is a global alternative investment manager. The firm invests across private equity, credit, and real assets, providing capital and strategic support to businesses.

Apple Inc. designs, manufactures, and markets smartphones, personal computers, tablets, wearables, and accessories. The company also offers various related services, including cloud services, digital content, and payment services.

Applied Materials, Inc. provides materials engineering solutions to manufacture semiconductors and displays. The company's products are used in the production of integrated circuits, flat panel displays, and solar photovoltaic cells. It operates through three segments: Semiconductor Systems, Applied Global Services, and Display and Adjacent Markets.

Aptiv PLC is a global technology and mobility architecture company. It designs, develops, and manufactures vehicle components; and provides electrical, electronic, and safety technology solutions to automotive and commercial vehicle manufacturers.
Arch Capital Group Ltd. is a global insurance and reinsurance company. It provides a wide range of property, casualty, and mortgage insurance and reinsurance products worldwide.

Archer-Daniels-Midland Company (ADM) connects crops to markets, transforming them into products for food, animal feed, industry, and energy. It is a global leader in agricultural processing and nutrition.

Arista Networks is a leading provider of data-driven, client to cloud networking for large data center, campus and routing environments. The company's award-winning platforms deliver availability, agility, automation, analytics and security through CloudVision and Arista EOS.

Arthur J. Gallagher & Co. is an insurance brokerage and risk management services firm. It provides insurance brokerage, consulting, and third-party claim settlement and administration services to corporations, public entities, and other organizations around the world.

Assurant, Inc. provides risk management solutions, primarily focusing on the housing and lifestyle markets. The company offers a range of insurance products and related services, including lender-placed insurance, manufactured housing insurance, and extended service contracts.

AT&T Inc. is a telecommunications holding company. It provides communications and digital entertainment services in the United States and internationally. The company operates through various segments, including communications, media, and Latin America.

Atmos Energy Corporation distributes, operates, and maintains natural gas pipeline and storage systems. It serves over three million distribution customers in several states. The company also provides natural gas transportation and storage services.

Autodesk, Inc. is a software corporation that makes software for the architecture, engineering, construction, manufacturing, media, and entertainment industries. It is best known for its AutoCAD software.

Automatic Data Processing, Inc. (ADP) provides cloud-based human capital management (HCM) solutions. It offers payroll services, HR management, talent management, benefits administration, and time and attendance tracking solutions to employers of various sizes.

AutoZone, Inc. is a retailer and distributor of automotive replacement parts and accessories in the Americas. It operates over 6,000 stores across the United States, Mexico, and Brazil. The company offers a wide range of products for cars, SUVs, vans, and light trucks.

AvalonBay Communities, Inc. is a real estate investment trust (REIT) focused on developing, redeveloping, acquiring, and managing high-quality apartment communities in leading metropolitan areas. The company emphasizes long-term value creation through strategic property management and development.

Avery Dennison Corporation is a global materials science and manufacturing company specializing in the design and manufacture of a wide variety of labeling and functional materials. Its products include pressure-sensitive materials, tags, labels, and tickets.

Axon Enterprise, Inc. develops, manufactures, and sells law enforcement and public safety products. It operates through two segments: Axon and TASER. The company's products include conducted energy weapons, body-worn cameras, and cloud-based software and services.

Baker Hughes is an energy technology company that provides equipment and services for the oil and gas industry. It designs, manufactures, and services products for oil and gas extraction, and also provides digital solutions for the energy sector.

Ball Corporation supplies innovative, sustainable aluminum packaging solutions for beverage, personal care, and household products customers, as well as aerospace and other technologies and services. The company operates globally, manufacturing metal beverage and aerosol containers.

Bank of America Corporation is a global financial institution providing a range of banking, investment, asset management, and other financial and risk management products and services to individuals, small- and middle-market businesses, and large corporations. It operates through various segments, including Consumer Banking, Global Wealth & Investment Management, Global Banking, and Global Markets.

Baxter International Inc. is a global medical technology company. It develops, manufactures, and markets a broad portfolio of products and services in areas such as kidney care, acute therapies, medication delivery, and surgical products.

Becton, Dickinson and Company (BDX) is a global medical technology company that develops, manufactures, and sells a range of medical devices, instrument systems, and reagents. The company serves healthcare institutions, life science researchers, clinical laboratories, industry, and the general public.

Berkshire Hathaway Inc. is a holding company owning subsidiaries engaged in various business activities. These include insurance, freight rail transportation, energy generation and distribution, manufacturing, retailing, and services.

Best Buy Co., Inc. is a multinational retailer of consumer electronics, home office products, entertainment software, appliances and related services. The company operates through stores and online under various brand names including Best Buy, Magnolia, and Pacific Sales.

Technology company involved in software, hardware, and cloud computing. They develop, license, and support a range of software products and services. Their offerings are used by consumers and businesses worldwide.

Biogen Inc. is a biotechnology company that discovers, develops, and delivers therapies for neurological and neurodegenerative diseases worldwide. The company's key products address multiple sclerosis, spinal muscular atrophy, and Alzheimer's disease, among others.

BlackRock, Inc. is a global investment management firm. It provides a range of investment and technology services to institutional and retail clients worldwide, helping them build savings and achieve their financial goals. BlackRock is the world's largest asset manager.

Blackstone Inc. is an alternative asset management company. It invests in private equity, real estate, credit, and hedge funds. The firm serves corporations, pension funds, insurance companies, and high-net-worth individuals.

The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation is a global investments company. It provides financial products and services to corporations, institutions and high-net-worth individuals. The company operates in more than 35 countries and is a leading provider of asset management and custody services.

The Boeing Company is an aerospace company. It designs, manufactures, and sells airplanes, rotorcraft, rockets, satellites, telecommunications equipment, and missiles worldwide. It also provides leasing and product support services.

Booking Holdings Inc. is the world's leading provider of online travel & related services, provided to consumers and local partners in more than 220 countries and territories through six primary consumer-facing brands: Booking.com, Priceline, Agoda, Rentalcars.com, KAYAK and OpenTable.

Boston Scientific Corporation develops, manufactures, and markets medical devices for use in various interventional medical specialties worldwide. The company's products are used in procedures including cardiac rhythm management, electrophysiology, and peripheral interventions.

Bristol-Myers Squibb is a global biopharmaceutical company focused on discovering, developing, and delivering innovative medicines for patients with serious diseases. Its primary focus areas include oncology, hematology, immunology, and cardiovascular disease.

Broadcom Inc. designs, develops, and supplies a range of semiconductor and infrastructure software solutions. Its products serve data center, networking, software, broadband, wireless, and storage markets.

Groupe Bruxelles Lambert (GBL) is a Belgian holding company with investments in various sectors, including energy, beverages, and healthcare. It holds significant stakes in companies like Imerys, Pernod Ricard, and Adidas.

Brown & Brown, Inc. is an insurance brokerage firm providing risk management solutions to businesses, corporations, governmental institutions, professional organizations, and individuals. The company offers a range of insurance products and services, including commercial property, casualty, employee benefits, and personal lines.

Berkshire Hathaway Inc. is a holding company owning subsidiaries engaged in various business activities. These include insurance, freight rail transportation, energy, services, manufacturing, retailing and others.

Builders FirstSource, Inc. manufactures and supplies building materials, manufactured components, and construction services to professional homebuilders, sub-contractors, remodelers, and consumers in the United States. They offer a range of products including lumber, millwork, windows, and doors.

Bunge Global SA operates as an agribusiness and food company worldwide. It operates through Merchandising, Processing, Refined and Specialty Oils, and Milling segments. The company is involved in the purchase, storage, transport, processing, and sale of agricultural commodities and commodity products.

Boston Properties, Inc. is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that develops, owns, and manages Class A office properties in select gateway markets. The company focuses on a relatively small number of large, modern, and high-quality properties in major metropolitan areas.

C.H. Robinson Worldwide, Inc. is a third-party logistics provider. The company offers freight transportation and logistics, outsourcing, and information services to over 100,000 customers through a network of offices in North America, Europe, Asia, South America, and Australia.

Cadence Design Systems, Inc. provides software, hardware, and services for designing and verifying complex electronic systems and integrated circuits. Their solutions are used by companies worldwide to develop a wide range of electronic products.

Caesars Entertainment, Inc. is a gaming and hospitality company. It operates casinos, hotels, and entertainment venues. The company also offers online sports betting and iGaming through its Caesars Sportsbook and iCasino platforms.

Camden Property Trust is a real estate company primarily engaged in the ownership, management, development, redevelopment, acquisition, and construction of multifamily apartment communities. The company focuses on high-growth markets across the United States.
Campbell Soup Company manufactures and markets branded food and beverage products. It operates through Meals & Beverages and Snacks segments, offering soups, sauces, snacks, and beverages.

Capital One Financial Corporation is a diversified financial services company. It offers a broad array of financial products and services to consumers, small businesses and commercial clients through various channels. These products and services include credit cards, banking, and auto loans.

Cardinal Health, Inc. is a distributor of pharmaceuticals and medical products, serving pharmacies, hospitals, and healthcare providers. The company also provides services to support the efficient delivery of healthcare.

CarMax Inc. is a used car retailer. The company operates through two segments: CarMax Sales and CarMax Auto Finance. CarMax Sales offers a range of used vehicles, while CarMax Auto Finance provides financing options to customers purchasing vehicles from CarMax.
Carnival Corporation & plc is a global cruise company. It operates a portfolio of cruise brands, offering a range of vacation experiences. The company sails to destinations around the world.

Carrier Global Corporation provides heating, ventilating, and air conditioning (HVAC), refrigeration, fire, security, and building automation technologies worldwide. It offers a broad range of products and services for residential, commercial, and industrial applications.

Caterpillar Inc. is the world's leading manufacturer of construction and mining equipment, diesel and natural gas engines, industrial gas turbines, and diesel-electric locomotives. The company also provides financial products and related services.

Cboe Global Markets, Inc. operates exchanges and provides trading solutions. It offers options, futures, U.S. and European equities, exchange-traded products (ETPs), global foreign exchange (FX) and multi-asset volatility products and services. The company also provides data solutions, indices and analytics.

CBRE Group, Inc. is a commercial real estate services and investment firm. It provides a range of services to commercial real estate owners, investors, and occupiers, including property management, leasing, valuation, and sales.

CDW Corporation is a leading multi-brand technology solutions provider to business, government, education and healthcare customers. A Fortune 500 company and member of the S&P 500 Index, CDW employs approximately 15,000 coworkers.

Cencora, Inc. (formerly AmerisourceBergen Corporation) is a leading global pharmaceutical solutions organization. It partners with pharmaceutical manufacturers and healthcare providers to improve access to medicines and enhance patient care.

Centene Corporation is a managed care enterprise that provides programs and services to government-sponsored and commercial healthcare programs. It focuses on individuals receiving benefits under Medicaid, Medicare, and other government subsidized programs, as well as commercial populations.

CenterPoint Energy, Inc. is a domestic energy delivery company that focuses on providing electric and natural gas services. It serves more than seven million metered customers primarily in Arkansas, Indiana, Louisiana, Minnesota, Mississippi, Ohio, Oklahoma, and Texas. The company also owns a 53.7% limited partner interest in Enable Midstream Partners, LP.

CF Industries Holdings, Inc. manufactures and distributes nitrogen and hydrogen products for clean energy, fertilizer, emissions abatement, and other industrial activities worldwide. It operates through two segments: Nitrogen Fertilizer and Hydrogen and Low Carbon Solutions.
UNK

Charles Schwab Corporation provides a full range of brokerage, banking and financial advisory services through its operating subsidiaries. Its services include financial planning, investment management, and wealth management solutions to individuals and institutions.

Charter Communications is a broadband connectivity company and cable operator serving residential and commercial customers in the United States. It offers a range of services, including internet, video, mobile, and voice, under the Spectrum brand.

Chevron Corporation is an American multinational energy corporation. It is engaged in integrated energy and chemical operations, exploring for, producing and transporting crude oil and natural gas; refining, marketing and distributing transportation fuels and lubricants; manufacturing and selling petrochemicals and additives; and developing technologies that enhance every aspect of the company’s business.

Chipotle Mexican Grill, Inc. operates restaurants serving a focused menu of burritos, tacos, bowls, and salads. The company emphasizes fresh ingredients and classic cooking methods. Chipotle has locations throughout the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, France, and Germany.

Cboe Global Markets operates exchanges and provides trading solutions. It offers options, futures, U.S. and European equities, exchange-traded products (ETPs), global foreign exchange (FX) and volatility products trading.

Church & Dwight Co., Inc. develops, manufactures, and markets a range of household, personal care, and specialty products. It operates through three segments: Consumer Domestic, Consumer International, and Specialty Products. The company's brands include ARM & HAMMER, TROJAN, OXICLEAN, and WATERPIK.

Cigna Corporation is a global health service company. It provides insurance and related products and services, including medical, dental, behavioral health, pharmacy benefits, and data analytics, primarily to employer groups and individuals.

Cincinnati Financial Corporation offers property and casualty insurance products. It operates through commercial lines, personal lines, and excess and surplus lines segments. The company also provides commercial fire, auto, and casualty insurance, as well as homeowners and auto policies.

Cintas Corporation provides corporate identity uniforms and related business services primarily in North America. It operates through two segments: Uniform Rental and Facility Services, and First Aid and Safety Services. The company designs, manufactures, and implements corporate identity uniform programs.

Cisco Systems, Inc. designs, manufactures, and sells networking hardware, software, and telecommunications equipment. It provides a broad range of solutions for networking, security, collaboration, and cloud computing. Cisco serves businesses of all sizes, public institutions, and service providers.

Citigroup Inc. is a global financial services company. It provides a range of financial products and services to consumers, corporations, governments, and institutions worldwide, including banking, credit cards, investment banking, and wealth management.

Citizens Financial Group, Inc. is a bank holding company. It provides retail and commercial banking products and services to individuals, small businesses, middle-market companies, and large corporations, primarily in the New England, Mid-Atlantic, and Midwest regions of the United States.

The Clorox Company is a multinational manufacturer and marketer of consumer and professional products. They offer a wide range of cleaning, household, and personal care products. Their brands include Clorox bleach, Pine-Sol cleaner, Liquid-Plumr clog remover, and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.

CME Group Inc. operates contract markets for trading futures and options on futures. It offers a range of benchmarks across major asset classes, including interest rates, equity indexes, foreign exchange, energy, agricultural commodities, and metals. The company also provides clearing and settlement services.

CMS Energy Corporation is an energy company. It operates primarily in Michigan, providing electricity and natural gas services. The company's operations include electric generation, transmission, and distribution, as well as natural gas distribution and storage.

The Coca-Cola Company is a beverage company. It manufactures, markets, and sells various nonalcoholic beverages, including sparkling soft drinks, water, sports drinks, juice, dairy, and plant-based beverages. It also offers beverage concentrates and syrups.

Cognizant Technology Solutions is a multinational information technology services and consulting company. It provides IT consulting, digital transformation, technology, and engineering services to businesses across various industries. The company helps clients modernize technology, reinvent processes and transform experiences.
Colgate-Palmolive Company is a global consumer products company. It focuses on the production, distribution, and sale of household, health care, personal care, and pet nutrition products.

Comcast Corporation is a global media and technology company. It operates through Cable Communications, Media, Studios, and Theme Parks segments, providing cable services, producing and distributing film and television content, and operating theme parks.

Conagra Brands, Inc. is a packaged foods company. It manufactures and markets branded and private label food products. Conagra's portfolio includes brands such as Birds Eye, Duncan Hines, Healthy Choice, Marie Callender's, and Reddi-wip.

ConocoPhillips explores for, produces, transports, and markets crude oil, natural gas, natural gas liquids, liquefied natural gas, and bitumen worldwide. It engages in the exploration and production of unconventional and conventional resources.

Consolidated Edison, Inc. is a holding company that provides energy-related services. The company delivers electricity, natural gas, and steam to customers in New York City and Westchester County, New York. It invests in renewable energy projects.
Constellation Brands, Inc. is a leading international producer and marketer of beer, wine, and spirits. Its portfolio includes brands like Corona, Modelo, Pacifico, Kim Crawford, and Meiomi.

Constellation Energy Corporation is a leading clean energy company. It produces and supplies energy, primarily electricity, through a diverse mix of nuclear, renewable, and natural gas generation facilities. The company serves homes, businesses, and public sector customers across the continental United States.

The Cooper Companies, Inc. is a global medical device company. It operates through two business units: CooperVision (CVI) and CooperSurgical (CSI). CVI manufactures and markets a wide range of contact lenses, while CSI provides medical devices, fertility and genomic solutions, and services to women's healthcare clinicians.

Copart, Inc. provides online auctions and vehicle remarketing services. It offers a platform for selling vehicles primarily to vehicle dismantlers, rebuilders, used vehicle dealers, exporters, and the general public.

Corning Incorporated is a leading innovator in materials science. For more than 170 years, Corning has applied its unparalleled expertise in specialty glass, ceramics, and optical physics to develop products that have created new industries and transformed people's lives.

CT Payments, Inc. provides payment processing and related technology solutions. The company facilitates electronic payments for merchants and businesses. It offers services such as credit and debit card processing, mobile payments, and point-of-sale systems.

Corteva, Inc. is an agricultural chemical and seed company. It develops and supplies germplasm and traits in corn, soybean and sunflower seeds. The company also offers products for weed and pest control, as well as digital solutions for agriculture.

CoStar Group, Inc. provides information, analytics, and online marketplace services to the commercial real estate industry. Its offerings include property information, marketing tools, and lead generation services for brokers, owners, and investors. The company also operates online marketplaces for apartments, businesses for sale, and land.

Costco Wholesale Corporation operates membership warehouses. It offers a wide selection of merchandise, plus specialty departments and exclusive member services. Costco's goal is to provide quality goods and services at the lowest possible prices.

Coterra Energy Inc. is an independent oil and gas company engaged in the development, exploration, and production of oil, natural gas, and natural gas liquids. The company operates primarily in the Marcellus Shale in Pennsylvania and the Permian Basin in West Texas and New Mexico.

CrowdStrike Holdings, Inc. is a cybersecurity technology company. It provides cloud-delivered protection across endpoints and cloud workloads, identity and data. The company's Falcon platform offers various modules, including threat intelligence, security and IT operations, and threat hunting.

Crown Castle International Corp. is a real estate investment trust (REIT) and provider of shared communications infrastructure in the United States. The company owns, operates, and leases cell towers, small cell networks, and fiber solutions.

CSX Corporation is a transportation company providing rail, intermodal and rail-to-truck transload services. Its rail network connects major population centers in 23 states east of the Mississippi River, the District of Columbia, and the Canadian provinces of Ontario and Quebec.

Cummins Inc. designs, manufactures, distributes, and services diesel and natural gas engines, electric and hybrid powertrains, and related components worldwide. The company also provides filtration, aftertreatment, turbochargers, fuel systems, controls, air handling systems, automated transmissions, electric power generation systems, and batteries.

CVS Health Corporation is a diversified healthcare company. It provides health services, insurance plans, and prescription drug services. The company operates through its Health Services, Pharmacy & Consumer Wellness, and Health Care Benefits segments.

Danaher Corporation designs, manufactures, and markets professional, medical, industrial, and commercial products and services. It operates through various segments including biotechnology, life sciences, and diagnostics, offering a diverse range of solutions for research, healthcare, and environmental applications.

Darden Restaurants, Inc. owns and operates full-service restaurants in the United States and Canada. Its portfolio includes Olive Garden, LongHorn Steakhouse, Cheddar's Scratch Kitchen, Yard House, and The Capital Grille.

DaVita Inc. is a kidney care company that provides dialysis services for patients with chronic kidney failure and end stage renal disease. The company operates kidney dialysis centers and provides related services, as well as providing integrated care and disease management services.

Day One Biopharmaceuticals, Inc. is a commercial-stage biopharmaceutical company dedicated to developing and commercializing targeted therapies for people of all ages with cancer. The company's focus is on pediatric cancers, addressing unmet needs in this patient population.

Deckers Outdoor Corporation designs, markets, and distributes footwear, apparel, and accessories. It operates through the HOKA, UGG, Teva, Sanuk, and Koolaburra brands, offering products for various activities and lifestyles.

Deere & Company is a manufacturer of agricultural, construction, and forestry machinery. It also provides financial services and other related activities. The company operates through its agriculture and turf, construction and forestry, and financial services segments.

Dell Technologies Inc. is a technology company that designs, develops, manufactures, markets, sells, and supports a range of products and services. Its offerings include personal computers, servers, data storage devices, and software, catering to both consumers and businesses.

Delta Air Lines, Inc. provides scheduled air transportation for passengers and cargo throughout the United States and internationally. It operates a network centered on hubs and key markets, connecting travelers across its extensive route system. The company also offers maintenance, repair, and overhaul services to third parties.

Devon Energy Corporation is an independent energy company engaged in exploring for, developing, and producing oil, natural gas, and natural gas liquids. The company's operations are primarily focused in the United States.

Dexcom, Inc. focuses on the design, development, and commercialization of continuous glucose monitoring (CGM) systems. These systems are used by people with diabetes and by healthcare providers to help manage glucose levels. Dexcom's products include sensors, transmitters, and receivers, as well as software and mobile apps for data analysis and sharing.

FANG is an acronym that refers to four popular and successful American technology companies: Facebook (now Meta), Amazon, Netflix, and Google (now Alphabet). These companies have been dominant forces in the tech industry and have significantly impacted various aspects of modern life, including social media, e-commerce, streaming entertainment, and internet search.

Digital Realty Trust, Inc. is a real estate investment trust that owns, acquires, develops and manages data centers. The company's facilities are designed to provide secure, reliable and scalable infrastructure to support the digital needs of its customers. Digital Realty serves a diverse range of industries, including cloud computing, technology, and financial services.

Discover Financial Services is a digital banking and payment services company. It offers credit cards, personal, student and home loans, and deposit products. The company also operates the Discover Global Network.

Dollar General Corporation is a discount retailer in the United States. The company offers a variety of merchandise, including consumables, seasonal items, home products, and apparel. Dollar General primarily targets low-income and rural communities.

Dollar Tree, Inc. operates discount variety retail stores. The company offers merchandise at fixed price points through its Dollar Tree and Family Dollar segments. Its stores offer a variety of everyday items, seasonal goods, and consumables.

Dominion Energy, Inc. is a major energy company that provides electricity and natural gas to millions of customers. The company operates through various segments, including Dominion Energy Virginia, Gas Distribution, and Dominion Energy South Carolina. Dominion Energy is involved in the production, transmission, and distribution of energy resources.

Domino's Pizza, Inc. operates as a pizza restaurant chain. It offers pizzas, as well as other food items and beverages. The company operates primarily through its company-owned stores and franchise stores.

DoorDash operates an online food ordering and delivery platform. It connects customers with local businesses, offering a wide range of products including meals, groceries, and convenience items. The company also provides logistics services to merchants through its DashMart platform.

Dover Corporation is a diversified global manufacturer delivering innovative equipment and components, specialty systems, and support services. Dover's business is conducted through five operating segments: Engineered Products, Clean Energy & Fueling, Imaging & Identification, Pumps & Process Solutions and Climate & Sustainability Technologies.

Dow Inc. is a materials science company, providing a range of products and solutions to various industries. It operates through segments like Packaging & Specialty Plastics, Industrial Intermediates & Infrastructure, and Performance Materials & Coatings.

D.R. Horton, Inc. is a homebuilding company in the United States. It is engaged in the construction and sale of single-family housing, with operations in multiple states across the country. The company also provides mortgage financing and title services to homebuyers.

Wabtec Corporation provides technology and services for the rail and transit industries worldwide. It offers a range of products and services, including locomotives, signaling and control systems, and digital solutions, aimed at improving safety, efficiency, and productivity.

Walgreens Boots Alliance is a global leader in retail pharmacy, offering convenient access to health and wellbeing services and trusted advice. The company operates retail pharmacies across the United States and Europe, and provides pharmaceutical wholesale and distribution services.

Walmart Inc. is a multinational retail corporation that operates a chain of hypermarkets, discount department stores, and grocery stores. It offers a wide assortment of merchandise and services at everyday low prices.

The Walt Disney Company is a diversified worldwide entertainment company. It operates through Parks, Experiences and Products; Entertainment; and Sports segments. Disney is known for its theme parks, film and television studios, and streaming services.

Warner Bros. Discovery is a global media and entertainment company. It creates and distributes content across various platforms, including film, television, and streaming. The company's portfolio includes well-known brands such as HBO, CNN, and Discovery.

Waste Management, Inc. is a leading provider of integrated waste management services in North America. The company provides collection, transfer, recycling and disposal services to residential, commercial, industrial and municipal customers. Waste Management also develops, operates and owns landfill gas-to-energy facilities.

Waters Corporation is a specialty measurement company focused on improving human health and well-being through laboratory analysis. The company designs, manufactures, sells, and services analytical workflow solutions, including chromatography, mass spectrometry, and software systems.

WEC Energy Group is an energy company focused on providing electricity and natural gas to customers in Wisconsin, Illinois, Michigan and Minnesota. The company operates through various segments, including Wisconsin Electric Power Company and Wisconsin Gas LLC.
Wells Fargo & Company is a diversified financial services company. It provides banking, investment and mortgage products and services, as well as consumer and commercial finance.

WELL Health Technologies Corp. is a Canadian healthcare company focused on consolidating and modernizing clinical and digital assets within the primary healthcare sector. It operates a network of outpatient medical clinics and provides digital health solutions.

West Pharmaceutical Services, Inc. is a leading manufacturer in the design and production of technologically advanced, high-quality, integrated containment and delivery systems for injectable medicines. The company partners with pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies to improve patient health.

Western Digital Corporation develops, manufactures, and sells data storage devices and solutions. The company offers a range of products, including hard disk drives (HDDs) and solid state drives (SSDs), used in computers, mobile devices, and data centers.

Weyerhaeuser Company is one of the world's largest private owners of timberlands. The company manages these timberlands on a sustainable basis, and manufactures wood, pulp and paper products. Weyerhaeuser also builds homes through its Weyerhaeuser Real Estate Company.

Williams-Sonoma, Inc. is a specialty retailer of high-quality products for the home. The company operates retail stores and direct-to-consumer channels under brands including Williams Sonoma, Pottery Barn, and West Elm.

The Williams Companies, Inc. is an energy infrastructure company. It focuses on connecting North America's significant hydrocarbon resource plays to growing markets for natural gas and natural gas liquids (NGLs). The company's operations include natural gas gathering, processing, and transmission; and NGL fractionation and storage.
WTW, formerly Willis Towers Watson, is a leading global advisory, broking and solutions company. It provides data-driven, insight-led solutions in the areas of people, risk and capital.

Workday, Inc. is a leading provider of enterprise cloud applications for finance and human resources. The company delivers solutions for financial management, human capital management, planning, and analytics, designed for complex organizations worldwide.
Wynn Resorts, Limited develops, owns, and operates luxury hotels and casinos. The company operates in Macau and Las Vegas, offering a range of gaming, entertainment, and retail amenities.

Xcel Energy Inc. is a public utility holding company that provides energy-related products and services. It operates through its subsidiaries to generate, purchase, transmit, distribute, and sell electricity and natural gas.

Xylem Inc. is a leading global water technology provider, enabling customers to transport, treat, test and efficiently use water in public utility, residential and commercial building services, industrial and agricultural settings. The company offers a wide range of products and services across the water cycle.
Yum! Brands, Inc. operates quick-service restaurants. It franchises or operates restaurants under the KFC, Pizza Hut, Taco Bell, and The Habit Burger Grill brands.

Zebra Technologies Corporation provides enterprise asset intelligence and tracking solutions. The company designs, manufactures, and sells a range of products including barcode scanners, mobile computers, RFID technology, and printing solutions.

Zimmer Biomet Holdings, Inc. designs, manufactures, and markets orthopedic products and dental reconstructive implants. The company provides knee and hip implants, as well as surgical and sports medicine products.

Zoetis Inc. discovers, develops, manufactures, and commercializes animal health medicines and vaccines, complemented by diagnostic products, genetic tests, biodevices and a range of services. The company serves veterinarians, livestock producers and people who raise and care for farm and companion animals.
